http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Laser-walls-for-unfenced-stretches-along-India-Pakistan-border/article14003662.ece

More than 40 vulnerable unfenced stretches along the India-Pakistan border will be covered by laser walls soon with the Home Ministry giving it a top priority to check infiltration in the wake of the Pathankot attack.A laser wall is a mechanism to detect objects passing the line of sight between the laser source and the detector. A laser beam over a river sets off a loud siren in case of a breach.